.TH "qmi_txn_wait" 9 "qmi_txn_wait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qmi_txn_wait \- wait for a response on a transaction
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qmi_txn_wait
.BI "(struct qmi_txn *txn "  ","
.BI "unsigned long timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "txn" 12
transaction handle
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout, in jiffies
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the transaction is decoded by the means of \fIei\fP and \fIc_struct\fP the return
value will be the returned value of \fBqmi_decode_message\fP, otherwise it's up
to the specified message handler to fill out the result.
.SH "RETURN"
the transaction response on success, negative errno on failure.
